## Library consumption (`npm run build`)

- **Output**: `dist/epds.js` (ESM), `dist/epds.css` (tokens + reset + extracted SFC styles), `dist/index.d.ts` (types). `public/` is not copied into `dist` for lib builds.
- **Peer dependency**: `vue` ^3.5 (see `package.json` `peerDependencies`).
- **Install in a host app**: `npm install epds` (when published) or `"epds": "file:../EPDS"` / workspace protocol for local monorepos — run `npm run build` in EPDS first so `dist/` exists.
- **Host app usage**:
  ```ts
  import { BaseButton, tokens } from 'epds'
  ```
  The package entry side-imports `epds.css`; bundlers should emit/load `dist/epds.css` automatically. Load **Roboto** (300/400/500/700) in the host app the same way as `index.html` / Storybook preview-head.
- **App shell vs library**: `npm run build` writes **`dist/`** (publish this for npm). `npm run build:app` writes **`dist-app/`** so it never overwrites the library output; use `vite preview` after `build:app` if you need to check the shell. Storybook is unchanged (`npm run storybook` / `build-storybook`).
- **New components**: add a barrel under `src/components/Name/` and register the export in `src/index.ts` (plus any public types already exported from the component `index.ts`).

## Components Built

### `TextBoxSM` — `src/components/TextBoxSM/`
- **Figma**: "Inputs/TextBoxSM" — single-line numeric/text input; 44px fixed height; ideal for price, payment, mileage entries
- **Props**: `label: string` (**required**), `modelValue?: string`, `prefix?: string` (left symbol, e.g. `$`), `suffix?: string` (right unit, e.g. `mi`), `name?: string`, `type?: string` (default `text`), `inputmode?: string`, `maxlength?: number`, `disabled?: boolean`, `error?: string`, `autocomplete?: string`
- **Emits**: `update:modelValue: [value: string]`
- **Anatomy**: 44px bordered box (`border-radius: 8px`, 2px border) · optional prefix span (Neutral40) · `<input>` flex-1 · optional suffix span (Neutral40) · floating label above · error below
- **Border**: 2px `--color-neutral-85` default → `--color-accent-30` focused → `--color-warning-50` error
- **Label**: `position: absolute; top: -20px; left: 0; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; color: --color-neutral-40`; `opacity: 0` in empty+unfocused state, `opacity: 1` when focused or has value
- **Placeholder**: `label` prop text, `--color-neutral-40` color — acts as visual label inside when unfocused/empty
- **Input text**: 16px Roboto Regular `--color-neutral-0`, `text-align: right`; prefix/suffix always `--color-neutral-40`
- **Error**: `position: absolute; top: 48px; left: 0; font-size: 12px; --color-warning-50`
- **Disabled**: no "disabled filled" visual state — disabled prop applies `opacity: --opacity-level-medium` to the control
- **Build notes**: Decimal commas auto-applied on 4/6-digit numbers (handled by consumer, not the component). 6-digit char max for numerics — pass `maxlength="6"`.
- **Stories**: Default, Focused, Filled, WithPrefix, WithPrefixFilled, WithSuffix, DisabledFilled, WithError, AllStates, Interactive, NumericUseCases

### `TextBoxLG` — `src/components/TextBoxLG/`
